Key Match Events: Padres outfielder Jurickson Profar made a jumping catch to rob a near home run in the first inning.
Fans threw baseballs, water bottles, and trash at Profar after he taunted a Dodgers fan.
Umpires paused the game several times to calm fans after the incidents.
Profar expressed that the situation felt 'dangerous' and had a similar experience with San Francisco Giants fans.
Post-Match Reflections: Profar discussed the dangerous nature of the fan interaction in his postgame interview.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Padres are limiting ticket sales to Dodgers fans for the remaining games to create a home-field advantage.
